ce:section.ce:para:
Endurance test measurements of the “write-read-erase-read” sequences were performed to observe the switching characteristics of the MIM-B devices as rewriteable flash memory devices, and the results are shown in Fig. 5
                     (a). The fabricated devices can be programed and erased up to 1100 cycles with significant distinction “ON/OFF” state as shown in Fig. 5(b). Fig. 5(c) and (d) illustrate the band diagrams of the MIM-B NVM device being programmed and erased, respectively, when the voltages are applied to the ITO electrode. While the device is programmed when the electrons are trapped in the GQDs, it is erased when the electrons in the GQDs are detrapped. A −2.5-V pulse is applied to the Ag NW electrode to inject electrons into the GQDs, resulting in the program process of the device, as shown in Fig. 5(c). A +5.0-V pulse is applied to the Ag NW electrode in an attempt to eject trapped electrons from the GQDs, resulting in the erase process, as shown in Fig. 5(d). The programmed current (I

                        ON
                     ) and the erased current (I

                        OFF
                     ) were read with −0.2 V applied to the ITO electrode for times up to 250 ms, and the results are shown in Fig. 5(a).
